<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 27 at 1:05PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...INTENSE SNOWFALL ACROSS THE SAGINAW VALLEY THIS AFTERNOON...
Areas of moderate to heavy snowfall will persist across the
Saginaw valley through 3 pm. High intensity snowfall rates of 1 to
2 inches per hour will be possible at times, leading to a rapid
accumulation of snow. In addition, visibility may drop to one
half mile or less. Motorists should remain aware of possible
changes in driving conditions this afternoon, as area roadways
become snow covered and slippery.</description>
